verbose_text: Using microarray analysis and RT-qPCR assays, it was found that SD increased the mRNA levels of protein kinase Czeta (PKCzeta) and calmodulin 3 (CALM3) and decreased those of the inducible nitric oxide synthase (iNOS) and wingless-type MMTV integration site family, member 5A (Wnt5a) genes significantly.
